import Page from "../common/Page" import classes from "./PostDetailPage.module.css" import { useParams } from 'react-router-dom'; import { useState, useEffect, useContext } from "react" import AuthContext from '../../../store/auth-context'; import {getRoomListApi} from '../../../../api/RoomApi' const landlord = { list: "50", cover: "https://funny-daffodil-350bc9.netlify.app/images/customer/team-1.jpg", address: "Liverpool, Canada", name: "Sargam S. Singh", icon: [, , , ], } const post = { id: 1, cover: "https://funny-daffodil-350bc9.netlify.app/images/list/p-1.png", name: "Red Carpet Real Estate", location: "210 Zirak Road, Canada", category: "For Rent", price: "$3,700", type: "Apartment", } const PostDetailPage = () => { const params = useParams() const id = params.id const authCtx = useContext(AuthContext) const [post, setPost] = useState({}) useEffect(() => { getRoomListApi(props.filter) .then((data) => { const tempData = [] data.data.forEach(item => { tempData.push({ cover: `https://funny-daffodil-350bc9.netlify.app/images/list/p-1.png`, totalPrice: item.rent_price + item.water_price + item.electricity_price + item.service_price, ...item }) }) setData(tempData) }) .catch((err) => { alert(err.message); }); }, [props.filter]) return (

{post.name}

{post.location}

) } export default PostDetailPage
